Descriptions. Pupa (n= 7 ). Total length 2.66–2.93 mm . Third abdominal segment 0.84-0.98 mm wide. Exuviae (
Fig. 22
) mostly yellowish. Abdominal margins slightly darker, rough, serrate.

Cephalothorax. Metathorax without spherical sensory pits. Respiratory organ (
Fig. 23
) trilobed, broadly flattened, about 1.5 times wider than long with spiracles along outer margin; anterior lobe elongate, lateral lobe elongate, as wide as the anterior; deep concavity between lateral, posterior lobes. Posterior lobe moderately wide.

Abdomen (
Fig. 24
). Chaetotaxy as in figure 24 . All sensilla very short. Segments expanded laterally with sharp extremities. Terminal process 0.43–0.49 mm long, serrate on margins, with spined apex, mesial seta on lateral margin.

Head (
Fig. 26
). Length 0.83–0.86 mm and width 0.88–0.98 mm . Antennae 0.45–0.50 mm long, about 0.6 times length of head, inserted apically on head, bearing three stout apical spines, one longer than others, about 0.5 times length of shaft. Mandible (
Fig. 25
), with two dorsal teeth, one large apical tooth, five short inner teeth. Mandibular lobe rounded, as dark as teeth. Outer margin serrate with two thick setae located apically, very short one at center, right beside long one; basally brush with seven stout, serrate spiniform setae. Mentum (
Fig. 27
) with 14–17 bold teeth, lateral ones gradually shorter. Posterolateral row of 14–15 spines, of which 7–8 located dorsally, 6–8 ventrally.

Body. Damaged, chaetotaxy not described. Anal segment cylindrical, about 1.5 times longer than wide. Siphon cylindrical (
Fig. 28
) 382–441 µm long, 99–147 µm wide, with pair of slender subapical setae, spiracular plate with two pairs of thick setae, another pair of slender ones.
